title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Just a sketch of the proof.</fr:p>
<fr:p><fr:strong>Step 1:</fr:strong> the fields <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R_{1}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R_{2}]]></fr:tex> are both character zero, i.e., there is no <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{R} + \cdots  + 1_{R}=0]]></fr:tex> (the sum of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex> copies of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{R}]]></fr:tex> vanishes). This is never true for either <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R_{1}]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R_{2}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p><fr:strong>Step 2:</fr:strong> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> is order-dense in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R_{i}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p><fr:strong>Step 3:</fr:strong> Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_{0}\colon  \mathbb {Q}\cap  R_{1}\to  R_{2}]]></fr:tex> be a function taking <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> in the sense that if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[q\in  R_{1}\cap \mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex>, then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_{0}(q)=q]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p>We extend this <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f_{0}]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  R_{1}\to  R_{2}]]></fr:tex> by <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(r)=\sup \{f(q)\mid  q<r\}]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r\in  R_{1}]]></fr:tex>. Then by the order-density of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex>, this <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is an order isomorphism.</fr:p>
<fr:p><fr:strong>Step 4:</fr:strong> The <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> we just constructed is a field isomorphism.</fr:p><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
